@NODE "Einf" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{i}Format @{ui} is a complete replacement for the original Format program (v40.105)
in your "SYS:System/" Drawer. Format uses @{"MUI" LINK "MUI"}!!!
Format should be 100% compatible to your old Format program.
Some additional features are:

 · Fontadaptive, resizeable Windows through MUI
 · Drag'n Drop
 · nice freely configurable Interface
 · Optional formatting without verify!
 · Select-Window for Devices! (WBStart without arguments..)
 · Support for the mfm.device. (CrossDos and CrossMac)
 · Configuration via Tooltypes

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

Please use the installer-script!

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Vor" "System requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"

 · OS 2.1 (v38) +
 · MUI 3.0 +

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Kompak" "Compatibility"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{i}Format@{ui} @{b}should@{ub} be 100% compatible to your old Format program.
Format also supports the mfm.device and so it's possible to format CrossDos and CrossMac Disks.

Inkompatibilities? Bugs? Suggestions? Drop @{"us" LINK "Adresse"} a few lines!

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Konfig" "Configuration"

Format can be configurated via Tooltypes.
The following Tooltypes can be used:

    VOLUMENAME={VOLUMENAME} (e.g. "EMPTY")

    VERIFY=ON or OFF

    TRASHCAN=ON or OFF

    FILESYS=OFS|FFS|INTL|DIRCACHE

these options can also be used with CLI!

@ENDNODE
